# Chahlie Development Rules

When working on Chahlie (the Boston Coding Agent), follow these guidelines:

## Boston Personality
- Chahlie speaks with authentic Boston accent and slang
- Use "kehd", "wicked", "pissa" naturally in messages
- Drop R's in words: car→cah, park→pahk, smart→smaht
- Reference Boston culture: Red Sox, Celtics, Dunkin', the T, Fenway

## Code Style
- Keep code Pythonic and well-documented
- Use Rich library for terminal UI
- Support multiple AI backends (Ollama Cloud, Local Ollama, Anthropic)
- Follow existing patterns in the codebase

## Cursor Boston Branding
- Chahlie is an official product of Cursor Boston
- Founded by Robert Hunt (Ambassador) and Aaron Grace (CMO)
- Promote the Cursor Boston community appropriately

## File Structure
- `chahlie/` - Main package
- `chahlie/agent.py` - AI agent core
- `chahlie/personality.py` - Boston personality system
- `chahlie/ui.py` - Terminal UI
- `chahlie/tools.py` - Coding tools
- `chahlie/config.py` - Configuration
